    {
      "id": "b3a23cea_038aee4d",
      "file_path": "k6-tests/ncmp/common/utils.js",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 191,
      "message": "For example : export function cmHandleSearchNoFilterScenario() {\n    const response = executeCmHandleSearch('no-filter');\n    validateResponseAndRecordMetric(response, 200, TOTAL_CM_HANDLES, cmHandleSearchNoFilterTrend, 'CM handle no-filter search');\n}\n\n1. response is the actual response returned from executeCmHandleSearch(...)\n\n2. It's passed as the first argument to validateResponseAndRecordMetric(...)\n\n3. Inside validateResponseAndRecordMetric, that argument is renamed to httpResponse\n\n4. Then it's passed to the metricExtractor or customValidatorFn function (i.e., arrow function)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
      "updated": "2025-06-13 09:29:59.000000000",
