      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "fca075c1_8f2b681c",
      "file_path": "k6-tests/ncmp/ncmp-test-runner.js",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 217,
      "message": "It’s a defensive check to ensure:\n\ntestProfile is defined and not empty or undefined.\n\nIt will work fine where:\n\nIf testProfile is undefined, testProfile === 'kpi' safely returns false.\n\nSo technically the testProfile && part is not strictly necessary.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
      "updated": "2025-06-13 09:29:59.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "8eddf8de_e75b3c5b",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "7f47daf7_f9599b24",
      "file_path": "k6-tests/ncmp/run-all-tests.sh",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 49,
      "message": "1. Central control flag – We set a clear, single flag that can be reused throughout the script.\n\n2. Avoids repeated string comparisons – Instead of checking \"$testProfile\" == \"kpi\" in multiple places.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
      "updated": "2025-06-13 09:29:59.000000000",
