      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "aef91406_1117fe5b",
      "file_path": "k6-tests/ncmp/run-all-tests.sh",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 76,
      "message": "To generate JavaScript trend declarations and threshold configs dynamically.\n\n1. Converts strings like \"http_req_duration\" → \"httpReqDuration\" (for valid JS variable names in K6).\n2. Starts building a config object with:\n\n            - trends: array of K6 Trend declarations\n\n            - thresholds: thresholds per metric\n3. Generates JS code for a K6 Trend like:\n\nexport let httpReqDurationTrend = new Trend('http_req_duration', true);\n4. Creates thresholds for each metric:\n\n      For http_req_failed: max failure rate\n\n          - For rate metrics: minimum avg\n\n          - For others (e.g., response time): maximum avg",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
